==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deuterozooid
<hw>Deu`ter*o*zo"oid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>deu`teros</grk> second + E. <ets>zooid</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the secondary, and usually sexual, zooids
produced by budding or fission from the primary zooids, in animals
having alternate generations. In the tapeworms, the joints are
deuterozooids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deuthydroguret</ent>⟦br⟧
